24:| D028 | M001 S08 planning | scanner autofix architecture | How Scanner Auto-Fix actions should be exposed and executed in the Rust port | Model Auto-Fix as a typed, registry-gated operation contract with an empty production registry for current parity; fake registries may be injected in tests, and future real operations must use plan preview, explicit confirmation, and pre-mutation revalidation before any file mutation. | The reference app contains Auto-Fix lifecycle UI labels but its production AUTO_FIXES registry is empty, so exposing disabled placeholders or unregistered mutations would diverge from parity and create unsafe write paths. A typed registry preserves the extension seam while fail-closing unsupported, stale, or tampered requests. | Yes, when a later slice explicitly scopes and tests real Auto-Fix operations. | agent |
